<subSubSection id="C322B8883A22FFBDFF0AEAABFD75FE70" lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="1169" pageId="34" pageNumber="1167" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A22FFBBFF0AEAABFEE7F9E2" blockId="34.[178,1085,1514,1594]" pageId="34" pageNumber="1167">
Description: Body length 
<quantity id="4CC046E63A22FFBBFDAFEAABFD24FA27" box="[535,658,1514,1536]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="34" pageNumber="1167" unit="mm" value="3.4" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.2">3.2-3.6 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="4CC046E63A22FFBBFCD1EAABFC52FA27" box="[873,996,1514,1535]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="34" pageNumber="1167" unit="mm" value="2.0" valueMax="2.1" valueMin="1.9">1.9-2.1 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: head blackish; remainder of body pale yellowish-brown; legs yellowish; antennae reddish-yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A23FFBAFF0AEF9AFB86FEF3" blockId="35.[178,1085,219,299]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">
Head (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A23FFBAFF40EF9AFEF3FF29" box="[248,325,219,241]" captionStart="Figs 95-101" captionStartId="34.[178,218,1432,1454]" captionTargetBox="[184,1091,212,1409]" captionTargetId="figure-1@34.[178,1091,212,1423]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 95-101: Lithocharis inermis nov.sp. (95-99) and &quot;Lithocharis&quot; gigantea FAUVEL, syntype (100-101): (95, 100) forebody; (96) male sternite VII; (97) male sternite VIII; (98-99) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; head (101). Scale bars: 95, 100-101: 1.0 mm; 96-99: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184214" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184214/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">Fig. 95</figureCitation>
) 1.06-1.09 times as broad as long; punctation extremely dense and very fine. Eyes conspicuously large, 1.6-1.9 times as long as postocular portion in dorsal view. Antennae approximately 
<quantity id="4CC046E63A23FFBAFE48EE54FD8BFEF3" box="[496,573,277,299]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
long; preapical antennomeres weakly transverse.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A23FFBAFF0AEE7AFCA8FE70" blockId="35.[178,1085,314,424]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A23FFBAFE9DEE7AFED9FE88" box="[293,367,314,337]" captionStart="Figs 95-101" captionStartId="34.[178,218,1432,1454]" captionTargetBox="[184,1091,212,1409]" captionTargetId="figure-1@34.[178,1091,212,1423]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 95-101: Lithocharis inermis nov.sp. (95-99) and &quot;Lithocharis&quot; gigantea FAUVEL, syntype (100-101): (95, 100) forebody; (96) male sternite VII; (97) male sternite VIII; (98-99) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; head (101). Scale bars: 95, 100-101: 1.0 mm; 96-99: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184214" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184214/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">Fig. 95</figureCitation>
) weakly oblong, approximately 1.03 times as long as broad and 0.92- 0.95 times as broad as head; posterior angles rounded, weakly marked; punctation similar to that of head, but slightly more distinct; midline with narrow impunctate band, in posterior half with fine furrow; interstices without microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A23FFBAFF0AEEF9FDE2FDD0" blockId="35.[178,1086,440,520]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A23FFBAFEBBEEF9FEE7FE16" box="[259,337,440,462]" captionStart="Figs 95-101" captionStartId="34.[178,218,1432,1454]" captionTargetBox="[184,1091,212,1409]" captionTargetId="figure-1@34.[178,1091,212,1423]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 95-101: Lithocharis inermis nov.sp. (95-99) and &quot;Lithocharis&quot; gigantea FAUVEL, syntype (100-101): (95, 100) forebody; (96) male sternite VII; (97) male sternite VIII; (98-99) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; head (101). Scale bars: 95, 100-101: 1.0 mm; 96-99: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184214" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184214/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">Fig. 95</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as pronotum; punctation very dense and fine. Hind wings present. Protarsomeres I-IV moderately dilated. Metatarsomere I nearly as long as the combined length of II and III.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF47BB8B3A23FFBAFF0AEAA6FDE7F999" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184216" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5184216" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184216/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168" startId="35.[178,218,1511,1533]" targetBox="[195,1064,536,1484]" targetPageId="35">
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A23FFBAFF0AEAA6FDE7F999" blockId="35.[178,1086,1511,1602]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A23FFBAFF0AEAA6FE86FA24" bold="true" box="[178,304,1511,1533]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">Figs 102-109</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A23FFBAFE87EAA9FDB4FA25" authority="Assing, 2015" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2015" box="[319,514,1512,1533]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latexcisa" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A23FFBAFE87EAA9FDB4FA25" box="[319,514,1512,1533]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">Lithocharis latexcisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27F8A6A3A23FFBAFDB4EAA9FDE7FA25" box="[524,593,1512,1533]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A23FFBAFDDDEAA6FD31FA24" bold="true" box="[613,647,1511,1532]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">102</emphasis>
) forebody; (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A23FFBAFCB9EAA6FC95FA24" bold="true" box="[769,803,1511,1532]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">103</emphasis>
) antenna; (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A23FFBAFC2AEAA6FC02FA24" bold="true" box="[914,948,1511,1532]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">104</emphasis>
) male sternite VII; (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A23FFBAFF5EEABFFEBEF9CB" bold="true" box="[230,264,1534,1555]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">105</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII; (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A23FFBAFE76EABFFDACF9CB" bold="true" box="[462,538,1534,1555]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">106-107</emphasis>
) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; median portion of aedeagus in ventral view (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A23FFBAFE0AE954FE62F9F2" bold="true" box="[434,468,1557,1578]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">108</emphasis>
); dorso-lateral apophysis in lateral view (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A23FFBAFCD2E954FC3AF9F2" bold="true" box="[874,908,1557,1578]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1168">109</emphasis>
). Scale bars: 102: 0.5 mm; 103-107: 0.2 mm; 108-109: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A24FFBDFF0AEF9AFCCEFED6" blockId="36.[178,1085,219,270]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169">Abdomen narrower than elytra; punctation fine and very dense; interstices with distinct microreticulation; posterior margin of tergite VII with palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A24FFBDFF0AEE5CFD75FE70" blockId="36.[178,1085,285,424]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169">
♂: sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A24FFBDFEE6EE5CFE1DFEEB" box="[350,427,285,307]" captionStart="Figs 95-101" captionStartId="34.[178,218,1432,1454]" captionTargetBox="[184,1091,212,1409]" captionTargetId="figure-1@34.[178,1091,212,1423]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 95-101: Lithocharis inermis nov.sp. (95-99) and &quot;Lithocharis&quot; gigantea FAUVEL, syntype (100-101): (95, 100) forebody; (96) male sternite VII; (97) male sternite VIII; (98-99) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; head (101). Scale bars: 95, 100-101: 1.0 mm; 96-99: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184214" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184214/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
) strongly transverse, posterior margin nearly truncate and with comb of approximately 30 moderately long palisade setae; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A24FFBDFC5CEE7AFB80FE89" box="[996,1078,315,337]" captionStart="Figs 95-101" captionStartId="34.[178,218,1432,1454]" captionTargetBox="[184,1091,212,1409]" captionTargetId="figure-1@34.[178,1091,212,1423]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 95-101: Lithocharis inermis nov.sp. (95-99) and &quot;Lithocharis&quot; gigantea FAUVEL, syntype (100-101): (95, 100) forebody; (96) male sternite VII; (97) male sternite VIII; (98-99) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; head (101). Scale bars: 95, 100-101: 1.0 mm; 96-99: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184214" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184214/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169">Fig. 97</figureCitation>
) strongly transverse and with broadly concave posterior margin, pubescence unmodified; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A24FFBDFE9DEE34FE2BFE53" box="[293,413,373,395]" captionStart="Figs 95-101" captionStartId="34.[178,218,1432,1454]" captionTargetBox="[184,1091,212,1409]" captionTargetId="figure-1@34.[178,1091,212,1423]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 95-101: Lithocharis inermis nov.sp. (95-99) and &quot;Lithocharis&quot; gigantea FAUVEL, syntype (100-101): (95, 100) forebody; (96) male sternite VII; (97) male sternite VIII; (98-99) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; head (101). Scale bars: 95, 100-101: 1.0 mm; 96-99: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184214" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184214/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169">Figs 98-99</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4CC046E63A24FFBDFE0BEE34FDA3FE53" box="[435,533,373,395]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169" unit="mm" value="0.55">0.55 mm</quantity>
long; dorso-lateral apophyses very long, apically distinctly extending beyond apex of ventral process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C322B8883A24FFBDFF0AEEF9FE0DFD60" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A24FFBDFF0AEEF9FE0DFD60" blockId="36.[178,1085,440,696]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169">
Comparative notes: This species is characterized particularly by the conspicuously large eyes, the oblong and slender pronotum, the shapes and chaetotaxy of the male sternites VII and VIII, as well as by the morphhology of the aedeagus, particularly the conspicuously long dorso-lateral apophyses. It is additionally distinguished from the similarly small syntopic 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A24FFBDFE15ED6CFD9CFD9A" authorityName="HERMAN" authorityYear="2003" box="[429,554,557,578]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sordidula">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A24FFBDFE15ED6CFD9CFD9A" box="[429,554,557,578]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169">L. sordidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the transverse head, the denser punctation of the head, the smaller pronotum (in relation to the head), the much more transverse sternite VII with more numerous and slightly shorter palisade setae at the posterior margin, and by the much more transverse male sternite VIII with a much larger and differently shaped posterior excision.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C322B8883A24FFBDFF0AED86FDA6FCC0" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A24FFBDFF0AED86FDA6FCC0" blockId="36.[178,1085,711,792]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169">
Distribution and natural history: Thetypelocalityissituatedin southern 
<collectingCountry id="F32FAB933A24FFBDFEA8EDA5FEDBFD22" box="[272,365,740,762]" name="Thailand" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169">Thailand</collectingCountry>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A24FFBDFECFEDA4FDA3FD21" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1928" box="[375,533,740,762]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distinguenda">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A24FFBDFECFEDA4FDA3FD21" box="[375,533,740,762]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169">L. distinguenda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A24FFBDFDFEEDA4FD74FD21" authorityName="HERMAN" authorityYear="2003" box="[582,706,740,762]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sordidula">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A24FFBDFDFEEDA4FD74FD21" box="[582,706,740,762]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169">L. sordidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found in the same locality. One of the 
<typeStatus id="548355A13A24FFBDFF4BEC43FEE2FCCF" box="[243,340,770,791]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1169">paratypes</typeStatus>
is slightly teneral.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
